  • Classes in io.github.nixtabyte.telegram.jtelebot.server used by io.github.nixtabyte.telegram.jtelebot.server.impl 
    Class and Description
    Command
    This interface represents a generic Telegram Bot command triggered by a User, and can be executed in order to make the Bot to perform a particular action.
    CommandDispatcher
    This interface represents a listener component that shall be able to execute or dispatch Command instances stored in an internal queue.
    CommandFactory
    This interface represents the centralized Factory class that would serve to create new Command instances when needed.
    CommandQueue
    This class represents a queue to store Command instances that could be later dispatched in a chronological order, depending on the executor implementation.
    CommandTask
    This interface represents an isolated task action that shall be able to handle the execution of an individual Command object.
    CommandWatcher
    This interface represents a listener component that sends polling requests to the Telegram Bot API service in order to fetch new Updates for the corresponding Bot.
    Service
    This interface represents a class that will act as a server, allowing it to be started or shut down.
